This paper deals with data privacy and security, specifically in relation to the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). The paper discusses mathematical concepts and their legal implications, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), cyber security (cs.CY), and information theory (cs.IT).
